In a bid to catch up with the rest of the world, fibre companies are rapidly covering more ground in the rollout of networks throughout South Africa. For many South Africans, gaining access to fibre broadband will open a world of opportunities that only reliable, ultra-high-speed connectivity can offer. To expand fibre infrastructure, fibre companies need the right tools and equipment. This is where IC Logistix (ICL) comes in. ICL offers tools and assistance of the highest standards, helping fibre businesses become more efficient and productive. For the period running from 1 September to 30 November 2019, ICL is offering an exciting combo deal which provides an assortment of equipment for efficient fibre rollouts. The products in the combo include: This entire package comes at an affordable price of R89,650.00 excl. VAT ICL also offers free toolkits with its Fukujira-70S+ and Fukujira-62S+ Splicer kits. Visit the IC Logistix kiosk at the FTTX Conference happening on 8-9 October at the Sandton Convention Centre in Johannesburg to take a look at their expansive range of products and services. They have a Fujikura-41S splicer kit up for grabs and many conference specials. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-322332" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IG-Logistix-jpeg.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="905" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IG-Logistix-jpeg.jpg 2481w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IG-Logistix-jpeg-283x400.jpg 283w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IG-Logistix-jpeg-768x1086.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IG-Logistix-jpeg-304x430.jpg 304w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IG-Logistix-jpeg-1200x1697.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> ICL is an importer and distributor of specialised technology and equipment for the fibre telecommunications market in Southern Africa and is a leader in the distribution of splicing and testing equipment. Their professional service and highly knowledgeable staff means you get the best solution for your needs. ICL offers a full turnkey solution for the installation and maintenance of optical fibre systems. Their range of products on offer include Fujikura arc-fusion splicing machines; AFL optical test, inspection and certification equipment; and Plumettaz blowing/floating machines. World-renowned brands in their portfolio include; Fujikura, AFL, Plumettaz, Ripley, Miller, AFL- Hyperscale, Softing, Divot, Fibertool, etc. Aftersales service is provided locally via an internationally accredited Calibration-Lab. For more information, contact sales at ICL on 011 521 2370 or iclsales@icl.co.za, or visit their website. This article was published in partnership with IC Logistix.